# Local development values come from `npx supabase status` after `npx supabase start`.
# Rule 3.6: ONLY the URL and anon key may be EXPO_PUBLIC_. Never put the service_role key here.
#
# To run against a HOSTED (cloud) Supabase project instead of the local stack — e.g. for an EAS
# build so the app doesn't need a dev server at all — replace these with the Project URL / anon key
# from your Supabase dashboard (Settings -> API). See docs/GUIDELINE.md §8 for the full walkthrough,
# and use EAS secrets (not this file) to bake them into a real build.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-local-anon-key
